<font color="#FF0000">REALITY CAN BE FUN, MAYBE</font><br>
<tt>Sat Sep 13  0:34:57 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Gentlemen,<br><br>
Haven't you heard the war is over (but not the trial) (hung jury) (mis-trial).  The continuing Tit for Tat <br>
is just going to perpetuate this dialogue.<br><br>
Doc, there is no even, ahead or behind in this.  Not even a <br>
finality.  Post on something of substance, besides an answer.  <br>
to information you detest.  Makes the answer something everyone <br>
detests.  Let rip with something from your world which we can work with. <br>
I responded to your pale rider post.  You got closer to truths than you <br>
can imagine.  We all courted death as a mistress.  Strange, but<br>
an interesting subject.  What do you think Doc.  Crazy, maybe.<br><br>
Cook, I love to hear your stories, accounts of your experiences.  <br>
They always seem to be appropriate to the situation.  I regret <br>
not writing my experiences down on paper as you did.  Ed, Art, others <br>
and myself enjoy them.  I am afraid some might object, but who cares.  <br>
I want to remember some of those experiences.  It has nothing to do with <br>
re-fighting the war.  I do not for a moment want to forget the reality <br>
of our time.<br><br>
I for one miss some of the fun we were have two weeks ago.  Why <br>
can't we enjoy this sight and grow with it at the same time?  <br>
I have always said, if it isn't fun it isn't worth doing.  We must <br>
not lose sight of the fact that we shouldn't do it at someone elses<br>
expense. I do not come to this sight each night to work.  I come <br>
because I value the friends I have made.<br><br>
Life is too short and we are burning precious time.<br><br>
Reality ensures that we must reserve the right to call an asshole <br>
an asshole when he/she deserves it.
<p><code>--   (SW) </code><p>


